	;;^DIC(3,"%D",1,0)
	;;=The degree and scope of each user's access is determined by information
	;;^DIC(3,"%D",2,0)
	;;=in this file.  It holds the encrypted access and verify codes
	;;^DIC(3,"%D",3,0)
	;;=which permit system access.  It may hold a termination date for user
	;;^DIC(3,"%D",4,0)
	;;=access, VA FileMan access codes and programmer access codes.
	;;^DIC(3,"%D",5,0)
	;;=For each user, it indicates the availability of options 
	;;^DIC(3,"%D",6,0)
	;;=(primary and secondary menus) and files (accessible
	;;^DIC(3,"%D",7,0)
	;;=files).  Via the Holder field of the Security Key File, users are
	;;^DIC(3,"%D",8,0)
	;;=able to unlock options.  Via the Name field of the Mail Box File, users
	;;^DIC(3,"%D",9,0)
	;;=are able to send and receive mail.  Other files similarly point to this
	;;^DIC(3,"%D",10,0)
	;;=one to permit editing help frames, auditing files, using the spooler,
	;;^DIC(3,"%D",11,0)
	;;=delegating menus, and so on.  Still other files point to this one to audit 
	;;^DIC(3,"%D",12,0)
	;;=user activity so that reports of sign-on times and option access may be
	;;^DIC(3,"%D",13,0)
	;;=generated by Service/Section or another user attribute.
